You could use the array method [`map`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/map) and merge the new and old object if the `id` matches or just return the old object as-is if the `id` doesn&#39;t match.

```js
updateSelection: item =&gt; {
  selection.update(items =&gt; {
    return items.map(i =&gt; (i.id === item.id ? { ...i, ...item } : i));
  });
};
```

Use the spread syntax to copy all the original keys, then add the one you want to modify:

```javascript
selection.update(items =&gt; {
  return {
     ...items,
     [item.id]: item
  }
});
```

