Complexity O(logN) by binary search

```

    int Arr[5]={4,5,1,2,3},l=0,r=4,mid,X,ans=-1;
    cin&gt;&gt;X;

```
Initialise the array *Arr* on which we are performing binary search.&lt;br&gt;
X is the number we are trying to find , l=0 and r=sizeof(Arr)-1 &lt;br&gt;
ans is index of X, -1 if not present in array.&lt;br&gt;

We have two condition when our given X will be in first half then we will update r to mid-1.&lt;br&gt;

**Case 1.** Rotation point is in the first half and X also. &lt;br&gt;
        *(Arr[l] &gt; Arr[mid] &amp;&amp; (X&gt;=Arr[l] || X&lt;=Arr[mid]))*&lt;br&gt;

It ensure that rotation point is in first half by Arr[l] &gt; Arr[mid] and if X&gt;=Arr[l] then X can only be in first half and X&lt;=Arr[mid] then also X can only be in first half.&lt;br&gt;

**Case 2.** Rotation point is in second half but X is in first half &lt;br&gt;
        *(Arr[l]&lt;=Arr[mid] &amp;&amp; (X&gt;=Arr[l] &amp;&amp; X&lt;=Arr[mid]))*&lt;br&gt;

If Arr[mid]==X then update answer and break loop.&lt;br&gt;
```
    while(l&lt;=r){
        cout&lt;&lt;l&lt;&lt;r&lt;&lt;&quot; &quot;;
        mid=(l+r)/2;
        if(Arr[mid]==X){
            ans=mid;
            break;
        }
        if((Arr[l] &gt; Arr[mid] &amp;&amp; (X&gt;=Arr[l] || X&lt;=Arr[mid])) 
           || (Arr[l]&lt;=Arr[mid] &amp;&amp; (X&gt;=Arr[l] &amp;&amp; X&lt;=Arr[mid])))
            r=mid-1;
        else
            l=mid+1;
    }
    cout&lt;&lt;ans;
```

